cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with text generation and machine translation, which are both sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses GANs and denoising autoencoders, which are popular deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves generating synthetic code, which falls under the domain of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of shared latent space and back-translation also suggests the involvement of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments involve working with image datasets, indicating the possibility of cs.CV (Computer Vision) being a relevant sub-category.
